modules.description: This module provides constant-time string comparison, byte-level search operations, hex encoding/decoding, ASCII case conversion, and integer/boolean utilities designed to prevent timing side-channel vulnerabilities. It operates on strings, bytes, 32-bit integers, and boolean values, ensuring execution time depends only on input length rather than content. These functions are particularly useful in security-critical contexts like cryptographic protocol implementations, where avoiding data-dependent timing variations is essential to prevent leakage of sensitive information.

This module provides direct equality and comparison operations for bigstrings, including byte-level comparisons in both big-endian and little-endian order. It supports searching and checking for specific byte values within a bigstring, with optional offset control. These functions are useful for low-level data processing tasks such as parsing binary formats or implementing network protocols.

This module implements efficient equality checks, byte-wise comparisons, and search operations for `bytes` values. It supports both big-endian and little-endian comparison modes, with optional length limiting, and allows searching or checking existence of bytes matching a predicate. Concrete use cases include binary protocol parsing, checksum validation, and low-level data comparison tasks.
